### Variables
@baseUrl = http://127.0.0.1:8000
@apiUrl = {{baseUrl}}/api/contactos
@authToken = suncar-token-2025

### 1. Crear un nuevo contacto
POST {{apiUrl}}/
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
    "telefono": "+593 99 123 4567",
    "correo": "juan.perez@email.com",
    "direccion": "Av. Amazonas N45-123, Quito, Ecuador"
}

### 2. Crear otro contacto
POST {{apiUrl}}/
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
    "telefono": "+593 98 987 6543",
    "correo": "maria.garcia@email.com",
    "direccion": "Calle 10 de Agosto #123, Guayaquil, Ecuador"
}

### 3. Obtener todos los contactos
GET {{apiUrl}}/
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 4. Obtener un contacto específico (reemplazar {contacto_id} con el ID real)
GET {{apiUrl}}/{contacto_id}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 5. Actualizar un contacto (reemplazar {contacto_id} con el ID real)
PUT {{apiUrl}}/{contacto_id}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
    "telefono": "+593 99 999 9999",
    "correo": "juan.perez.actualizado@email.com",
    "direccion": "Nueva Dirección #456, Quito, Ecuador"
}

### 6. Eliminar un contacto (reemplazar {contacto_id} con el ID real)
DELETE {{apiUrl}}/{contacto_id}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
